Minister in the Presidency Jeff Radebe has apologised for his involvement in a sex text scandal.Radebe was in Port Elizabeth where he addressed ANC officials from the Sarah Baartman region about policy discussion documents on Sunday.Social media was abuzz after the Sunday Times reported that Radebe was in hot water for raunchy text and e-mail communication in which he asked for nude pictures of a 29-year-old Union Buildings staffer Siyasanga Mbambani.SA politicians and 'sex scandals'While Radebe a 64-year-old minister dodged questions about his messages he referred all queries to his spokesman.His spokesman Phillip Musekwa said: The minister deeply regrets that the exchanges took place in the first place. He is worried about the welfare of the woman who is implicated. She will take the social media pressure of what is now out there. Mboweni warns about 'dirty political game' in the run-up to electionsMusekwa said Radebe would like to apologise to the country Mbambani her family and his own wife and children.He said Radebe admitted the incident and said it was poor judgment on hisSenior minister's 'sex scandal' spawns memes on social media 